dcterms:creator: A. Cully
J. Clune
D. Tarapore
J.-B. Mouret
dcterms:description: MAP-Elites is a quality diversity algorithm that uses a multidimensional grid-like archive as a phenotypic niching space, allowing for the generation of diverse, high-performing solution sets in robotic domains.
dcterms:title: MAP-Elites

dcterms:creator: K. O. Stanley
dcterms:description: Compositional Pattern Producing Networks (CPPNs) are used to directly insert geometrical abstractions into developmental encodings, allowing for the generation of complex shapes through mathematical functions.
dcterms:title: Compositional Pattern Producing Networks (CPPNs)

dcterms:creator: J. von Neumann
dcterms:description: Cellular Automata (CA) are developmental encodings that evolve over time based on simple rules, allowing for complex patterns to emerge from local interactions.
dcterms:title: Cellular Automata (CA)

dcterms:creator: I. Rechenberg
dcterms:description: Direct Encoding is a straightforward representation method where each genome directly maps to a phenotype, allowing for high-dimensional solutions but potentially slow convergence.
dcterms:title: Direct Encoding

dcterms:creator: V. Modrak
R. S. Pandian
P. Semanco
dcterms:description: Dictionary-based Encoding reduces the dimensionality of the search space by using a dictionary of building blocks to generate solutions, commonly applied in layout design optimization.
dcterms:title: Dictionary-based Encoding

dcterms:creator: H. Sobieczky
dcterms:description: Parametric Encoding allows for high control over design parameters, commonly used in engineering design to define local shape features.
dcterms:title: Parametric Encoding

dcterms:creator: J. E. Auerbach
J. C. Bongard
dcterms:description: Evolving CPPNs involves using compositional pattern producing networks to generate three-dimensional physical structures, demonstrating the application of CPPNs in physical design.
dcterms:title: Evolving CPPNs

dcterms:creator: X. Xu
C. Yin
W. Wang
N. Xu
T. Hong
Q. Li
dcterms:description: Genetic Algorithm-driven Urban Block Design utilizes genetic algorithms to optimize urban layouts, focusing on outdoor comfort and urban morphology.
dcterms:title: Genetic Algorithm-driven Urban Block Design
